A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing January 23, 2025, as Doula Day at the state capitol; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, a doula is a non-clinical support person who provides care to improve perinatal
3 health outcomes for laboring, birthing, and postpartum individuals, as well as loss support;
4 and
5 WHEREAS, the hallmarks of doula support emphasize community-based interpersonal
6 relationships, health promotion through preventative care, childbirth and health education,
7 emotional support, and the improvement of health outcomes; and
8 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia has a rich history of mothers, grandmothers, aunts, sisters,
9 or other close individuals attending births as supportive figures, and research shows that even
10 without formal training, this support can significantly decrease the likelihood of cesarean
11 sections, shorten labor times, and improve the birthing experience; and
12 WHEREAS, throughout history and across cultures, community-chosen doulas have been
13 revered for their roles in supporting birthing individuals, and Georgia's doulas and doula
14 agencies continue this legacy by training new doulas and providing support for those in need
15 during significant life events; and
